text: Don't invest in stock markets if you can't read financial statements on your own. And reading financial statements is not easy. Chartered accounts spent their whole life being proficient in reading them. It's not all about numbers that you have to read in a financial statements, you have to decipher whether a company is juggling the number or not to present a rosy picture to you. You have see what company is hiding from investors.How  Satyam a big tech company duped its investors is a case in point. Investing through mutual fund also has its limitations. Don't expect stock market will always give you handsome returns year after year.
